First Lady Michelle Obama will be traveling to Liberia, Morocco, and Spain as part of the Let Girls Learn initiative. In Liberia, she will visit a Peace Corps Training Facility and a school in Unification Town to discuss the obstacles girls face in attaining an education. In Morocco, she will participate in a conversation with adolescent girls and highlight commitments made by the US Government to help girls in Morocco go to school. In Spain, she will deliver a speech on Let Girls Learn and meet with Her Majesty Queen Letizia. The purpose of the trip is to highlight the US Government's work to help adolescent girls worldwide fulfill their promise and stay in school.